Friday August 30th 2013 12:08 pm -04:00,You can get started by using model builder in ArcMap or ArcCatalog. For instance you can create a simple model like a buffer or intersection and export the model to a python module. Once you open the python module you can start learning how to use the language to script more complex GIS operations. If you dig inside ArcGIS subfolders youll find several python modules that perform spatial statistics for example. The nice part is that you can apply the logic of programming with python with other GIS software as well.,None,1
